  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] After the liquidation of the ghetto, after the, the ghetto population was silenced, those that were killed were lying in the streets of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The streets of the ghetto looked like an outdoor morgue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we know that-- also I was not at the time in the ghetto, but I know that because after the three, four days, Schindler was ordered to deliver the 100 of us to the concentration camp of Krakau-Plaszow, where not only the 100 of us were shipped, but those remnants that survived the liquidation of the Cracow ghetto were also shipped to the same concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those remnants would tell us on what took place in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, at the same time, when we arrived there, we could, we could see the dump trucks of bodies arriving [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] with bodies that they cleaned up from the ghetto itself.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were simply cleaning up the ghetto and throwing the bodies on those dump trucks and bringing them into the Krakau-Plaszow concentration camp where there were open pits prepared for them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were dumping these bodies into the, into those pits.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember that not only myself but many people that were in my group would, at that time, think that possibly our families are arriving in that manner, that they were, in fact, possibly killed in the ghetto, and they are being dumped into the open pits.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the people that we knew, a friend of mine and my older brother's, also told me a story that he witnessed in the ghetto itself during the liquidation, that my brother was on one side of the street when he noticed that the rest of the family is on the other side of the street.",
      "word_count": 57
    }
  ],
